headline: Is It Too Late To Consider BlackRock After Its Strong Multi Year Share Price Run?
summary: If you are wondering whether BlackRock is still a smart buy at these levels or if the upside has already been priced in, you are not alone. That is exactly what we are going to unpack here. The stock has climbed 7.0% year to date and 5.2% over the last year, with a 67.2% gain over three years and 75.7% over five years, even though the last month has been relatively flat at -0.4% after a modest 1.6% move this past week. headline: Green Stocks Are Big Winners as Tech Boom Drives Energy Demand
summary: Instead, the sector is booming as artificial intelligence powers massive demand for all kinds of energy.  The S&P Global Clean Energy Transition Index has rallied  this year, handily beating a  advance in the S&P 500 Index.  It’s also outpacing an  gain in the S&P Global Oil Index, which was expected to be a big winner on the back of Trump’s “drill, baby, drill” agenda.
